OL,3,CMore than 280,000 crimes unrecorded by
OL,4,Cpolice last year, watchdog finds
OL,6,FMore than 280,000 crimes went
OL,7,Funrecorded by police last year, with
OL,8,F"unacceptably low" numbers of anti-
OL,9,Fsocial behaviour offences being
OL,10,Fofficially documented.
OL,12,FWatchdog His Majesty's Inspectorate of
OL,13,FConstabulary and Fire and Rescue
OL,14,FServices (HMICFRS) found 94.8% of
OL,15,Fcrimes were recorded by forces in
OL,16,FEngland and Wales in the year to March
OL,17,F31, up from 80.5% in 2014.
OL,19,FWhile it praised the increase, this
OL,20,Fstill meant that more than 285,000
OL,21,Foffences were not recorded.
