OL,3,CMore than 280,000 crimes unrecorded by
OL,4,Cpolice last year, watchdog finds
OL,6,FThe watchdog found that only 78% of
OL,7,Fcrimes on average are recorded within
OL,8,F24 hours, and stressed that officers
OL,9,Fshould record offences at the earliest
OL,10,Fopportunity.
OL,12,FSample cases audited between 2021 to
OL,13,F2025 showed that five forces recorded
OL,14,Fless than 40% of crimes within 24
OL,15,Fhours, while one only achieved 2.6%
OL,16,Fand took more than a week to record
OL,17,Fmost offences.
