OL,3,CMore than 280,000 crimes unrecorded by
OL,4,Cpolice last year, watchdog finds
OL,6,FHis Majesty's Inspector of
OL,7,FConstabulary Roy Wilsher said: "For
OL,8,Fthe public to have trust and
OL,9,Fconfidence in policing, they need to
OL,10,Fknow that when they report a crime,
OL,11,Fthe police will record it accurately
OL,12,Fand without delay.
OL,14,F"Correctly recording these crimes
OL,15,Fmeans forces can quickly allocate
OL,16,Fcases and begin investigations
OL,17,Fpromptly.
